Advanced Properties and Concepts of HTML
1. HTML Attributes

Attributes provide additional information about an element and modify its behavior.

Syntax: <tag attribute="value">

Examples of common attributes:

id – Unique identifier for an element

class – Assigns a class for CSS or JS

src – Specifies source for images or media

href – Specifies link destination

alt – Provides alternative text for images

title – Tooltip text

style – Inline CSS for styling

2. HTML Comments

Comments are ignored by browsers and used for documentation.

Syntax: <!-- This is a comment -->

3. HTML Entities

Used to display special characters that have reserved meanings in HTML.

Examples:

&lt; → <

&gt; → >

&amp; → &

&quot; → "

&copy; → ©

4. HTML Colors and Styles

HTML supports colors via:

Color Names: red, blue, green

Hex Codes: #FF0000 (red)

RGB Values: rgb(255,0,0)

Inline styling using style attribute, e.g., <p style="color:blue; font-size:16px;">Text</p>

5. HTML Forms

Forms are used to collect user input.

Key form elements:

<input> – Text, password, checkbox, radio, file, etc.

<textarea> – Multiline text input

<button> – Submit or action button

<select> & <option> – Dropdown menus

Attributes include name, value, placeholder, required, maxlength

6. HTML Tables

Tables structure data in rows and columns.

Key tags:

<table> – Table container

<tr> – Table row

<th> – Table header cell

<td> – Table data cell

Attributes like border, cellpadding, cellspacing, colspan, rowspan

7. HTML Media

Embeds audio, video, and interactive media.

<audio> – Play sound files (mp3, ogg)

<video> – Display video (mp4, webm)

<source> – Multiple media formats for fallback

<iframe> – Embed other web pages

8. HTML Semantic Elements

Introduced in HTML5 for meaningful structure:

<header> – Header section

<footer> – Footer section

<article> – Self-contained content

<section> – Thematic grouping

<nav> – Navigation links

<aside> – Sidebar content

<main> – Primary content

9. HTML5 APIs and Features

HTML5 introduced APIs for advanced web functionality:

Canvas API – Draw graphics and animations

Geolocation API – Get user location

Local Storage & Session Storage – Store data in browser

Drag & Drop API – Drag items on page

Web Workers – Background scripts

Audio/Video API – Media manipulation

10. HTML Links

Internal Links: Navigate within the same page (#section1)

External Links: Navigate to other websites (https://example.com)

Anchor Tag <a> Attributes: target="_blank", rel="noopener", download
